[Alytus is a city situated in southern Lithuania; it is the capital of Alytus county (maps at http://www.fallingrain.com/world/LH/56/Alytus.html and http://healthmap.org/r/9NLt).

Belarus, to the south east of Lithuania, reported 2 outbreaks of African swine fever (ASF) during 2013, one of them close to the border with Lithuania (see OIE: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/Diseaseoutbreakmaps; select ASF, start at 2011, zoom in to the region).

Lithuania's other neighboring countries, Poland (south west) and Latvia (north) are regarded as free of ASF; see political map at http://www.mapsofworld.com/lithuania/lithuania-political-map.html.

Russia, further to the east, has suffered 2 widely spread ASF epizootics since 2007, and declared the disease resolved as of 16 Dec 2013 (report submitted 25 Dec 2013).

Lithuania has, according to the OIE data, maintained throughout the years its status as free of ASF. Details and official results of the current laboratory and epidemiological investigations into the boar mortalities, with special attention to classical and African swine fever, would be helpful, hopefully diagnosing the causative agent(s). - Mod.AS]
